  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (residual-risk gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A known limitation regarding turbulence model accuracy in the impeller tip-gap region is acknowledged in the validation narrative; the decision record states that residual risk is acceptable without providing a supporting rationale for that acceptability determination.",
