    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou1-pump-head-validation",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump head and flow rate validation against FDA benchmark experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted pump head matched experimental measurements within 8% across all five operating points. Hemolysis index predictions fell within the experimental scatter band for four of five conditions. At the highest impeller speed (3500 rpm, 2 L/min), the model over-predicted the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) by 14%, attributed to known limitations in the k-omega SST turbulence closure in the tip-gap shear layer. This edge case is not fully covered by the current validation matrix. The deviation is noted; the overall validation is considered adequate for the COU."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou1-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) analysis performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 11.7M, 28.4M cells). GCI for NIH quantity of interest was 3.1% on the medium mesh, satisfying the project threshold of 5%. Richardson extrapolation confirmed asymptotic convergence. Discretization error is adequately characterized for MRL 2 requirements."
    },
